{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"49cc7f21-a4e1-4bb9-bab1-ea4ec0e9b320","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n\n// For Theory:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest(int x) { }\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\nKey differences: xUnit uses a `Skip` property on the test attribute itself, while MSTest/NUnit use a separate `[Ignore]` attribute and TUnit uses `[Skip]`. All four support a reason string.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b310b233-958b-4001-8563-c24a82385ddf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question about test framework APIs. Let me provide a concise answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":290,"requestId":"A028:E52A2:1845757:1B90C36:69FE8A58"},"id":"fb5ab3df-dd55-407d-b526-17a58ac064a9","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:14:07.201Z","parentId":"e6446e47-e045-42f2-81d0-0ce05142faff"}
